==English==
===Noun===
'''hysteresis'''
{{wikipedia}}

#A property of a [[control]] system such that the [[output]] value is not a strict function of the [[input]], but also incorporates some time [[lag]], [[delay]], or history dependence, and in particular when the [[response]] for an [[decrease]] in the input variable is different from the response for a [[increase]].  For example, a [[thermostat]] with a nominal setpoint of 75° might switch the controlled heat source on when the temperature drops below 74°, and off when it rises above 76°.

